The paper deals with motion planning for robots, which is a core problem in robotics and falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on sampling and precomputing a roadmap, which involves computational geometry and optimization techniques, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions simulations involving visual perception and image processing, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
